My favourite rainbows are the quiet ones. They do not shout like thunder or flash like lightning. They just appear, soft and shy, after a heavy summer shower.

I like them best when I am walking home from school. The sky is still grey and heavy, but the sun is trying to peek through. Suddenly, a faint arc appears above the rooftops. It is not bright like a toy. It is pale, like watercolour paint on wet paper.

I stop and look up. The colours are gentle: a soft pink, a pale yellow, and a light blue. They seem to touch the tops of the old oak trees in the park. For a moment, the world feels calm. The puddles on the pavement reflect the sky, making it look like the ground is floating.

I do not need to make a wish. I just watch. These rainbows are like a secret gift from the clouds. They remind me that even after the gloomiest days, something beautiful can happen. I smile, pull my coat tighter, and keep walking, knowing the magic is still there, waiting for the next drop of rain. [end of text]


